---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '@/components/primitives/Section.astro';
import Prose from '@/components/primitives/Prose.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '@/components/primitives/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { SITE } from '@/site.config';

const crumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Privacy', href: '/privacy' },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  titleFull="Privacy policy | Murikah"
  description="How Murikah collects, uses and protects personal data, and your rights under the Kenya Data Protection Act."
>
  <Section tone="surface" aria-labelledby="page-title">
    <Breadcrumb items={crumbs} class="mb-6" />
    <h1 id="page-title" class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl">Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-slate">Last updated: {'{{LEGAL: insert date}}'}</p>

    <div
      class="mt-6 rounded-card border border-hairline bg-paper p-4 text-sm text-slate"
      role="note"
    >
      <strong class="text-navy">{'{{LEGAL REVIEW REQUIRED}}'}</strong> This is a plain-English template.
      It must be reviewed and finalised by qualified counsel before launch.
    </div>

    <Prose class="mt-10">
      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Murikah ("we", "us") is the data controller for personal data collected through this
        website. For any privacy question, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect only what we need to respond to you and run the site:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Details you submit through the contact form: your name, organisation, role, email and
          message.
        </li>
        <li>Your email address if you subscribe to updates or request a checklist.</li>
        <li>Basic, privacy-respecting analytics about how the site is used.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why we use it, and our lawful basis</h2>
      <p>
        We use contact details to reply to enquiries and provide the services you ask about, and to
        send updates you have asked for. We rely on your consent for marketing emails, and on our
        legitimate interest in responding to enquiries and keeping the site secure. You can withdraw
        consent at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>
        We keep personal data only as long as we need it for the purpose it was collected, and then
        delete it. {'{{LEGAL: confirm specific retention periods}}'}
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights under the Kenya Data Protection Act</h2>
      <p>
        Under the Data Protection Act, 2019 you have the right to be informed, to access your data,
        to have it corrected or deleted, to object to certain processing, and to data portability.
        To exercise any of these, email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>. You may
        also complain to the Office of the Data Protection Commissioner (ODPC).
      </p>

      <h2>Demo sandbox and assistant</h2>
      <p>
        The Labs sandbox and the site assistant run on sample data only, with no real client systems
        or data involved. To operate and protect these features we briefly process and retain a
        small amount of technical data, including an anonymous session identifier, a hashed (not
        raw) IP address, and a short record of demo runs and assistant messages. Demo data is
        deleted within 24 hours and assistant logs within 30 days. Please do not enter real personal
        or confidential client information into the demos or the assistant.
      </p>

      <h2>Service providers</h2>
      <p>
        We use a small number of trusted providers to operate the site and our email, for example
        hosting and email delivery. They process data on our instructions, under written terms.
        {' '}{'{{LEGAL: list processors}}'}
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We keep cookies to a minimum and use analytics that respect your privacy. Where consent is
        required for non-essential cookies, we ask for it. {
          '{{LEGAL: confirm cookie/analytics tooling}}'
        }
      </p>

      <h2>ODPC registration</h2>
      <p>
        Murikah is registered as a data controller with the Office of the Data Protection
        Commissioner. {'{{LEGAL: insert ODPC registration number}}'}
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
